# asus-merlin-acme-ca domains configuration
# Location: /jffs/.le/domains
#
# Format: domain1|domain2|domain3|...
# - One certificate per line
# - Domains separated by pipes (|)
# - Supports wildcards (*.domain.com)
# - First non-wildcard domain becomes certificate directory name
# - Comments start with #
# - Empty lines are ignored

# Example 1: Wildcard certificate with base domain
# This creates a certificate valid for:
#   - yourdomain.com
#   - *.yourdomain.com (any subdomain)
*.yourdomain.com|yourdomain.com

# Example 2: Multiple specific subdomains (no wildcard)
# Useful when you only need specific subdomains
# www.example.com|api.example.com|mail.example.com

# Example 3: Mixed - wildcard plus specific subdomains
# Sometimes useful for clarity or specific needs
# *.yourdomain.com|yourdomain.com|www.yourdomain.com

# Example 4: Multiple certificates (one per line)
# Each line creates a separate certificate
# *.domain1.com|domain1.com
# *.domain2.com|domain2.com

# Example 5: Single domain (no wildcard)
# For simple cases where you don't need wildcards
# myrouter.dyndns.org
